{"created": "2025-12-10T16:22:04.492890+00:00", "modified": "2025-12-10T16:22:04.838950+00:00", "id": 17882310, "conceptrecid": "17882309", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.17882310", "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.17882309", "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17882310", "metadata": {"title": "Recursive Geometric Entropy: A Unified Framework for Information-Theoretic Shape Analysis", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.17882310", "publication_date": "2025-12-10", "description": "<p>We introduce Recursive Geometric Entropy (RGE), a specialized application of Recursive Entropy Calculus to geometric systems, establishing fundamental connections between&nbsp;geometric structure and information content through recursive subdivision. Building on the&nbsp;general REC framework, we derive concrete results for specific shape classes. For geometryrespecting radial refinements, we prove that entropy grows with a universal slope C = 1&nbsp;independent of shape, while the shape-dependent offset h\u03a9 serves as a geometric invariant. We derive closed-form expressions for standard shapes (disk: h2 &asymp; &minus;0.279, sphere:&nbsp;h2 &asymp; &minus;0.623, cone: h2 &asymp; &minus;0.180) and explain the observed transient &ldquo;1.25 resonance&rdquo; as&nbsp;a finite-depth phenomenon. For congruent self-similar subdivisions, we establish C = log2b&nbsp;where b is the branching factor, revealing deep connections between symmetry and information growth through prime factorizations. Computational validation achieves O(1/d)&nbsp;convergence using analytical methods. Applications span computational geometry, machine&nbsp;learning, materials science, and financial mathematics.</p>\n<p>Keywords:</p>", "access_right": "open", "creators": [{"name": "Reid, Steven", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["recursive entropy", "geometric information theory", "shape invariants", "subdivision algorithms", "differential entropy", "symmetry groups", "computational geometry", "multiscale entropy"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "10.5281/ZENODO.17862831", "relation": "isPartOf", "resource_type": "publication-preprint", "scheme": "doi"}], "resource_type": {"title": "Preprint", "type": "publication", "subtype": "preprint"}, "license": {"id": "cc-by-4.0"}, "relations": {"version": [{"index": 0, "is_last": true, "parent": {"pid_type": "recid", "pid_value": "17882309"}}]}}, "title": "Recursive Geometric Entropy: A Unified Framework for Information-Theoretic Shape Analysis", "links": {"self": "https://zenodo.org/api/records/17882310", "self_html": "https://zenodo.org/records/17882310", "preview_html": "https://zenodo.org/records/17882310?preview=1", "doi": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17882310", "self_doi": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17882310", "self_doi_html": "https://zenodo.org/doi/10.5281/zenodo.17882310", "reserve_doi": "https://zenodo.org/api/records/17882310/draft/pids/doi", "parent": "https://zenodo.org/api/records/17882309", "parent_html": "https://zenodo.org/records/17882309", "parent_doi": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17882309", "parent_doi_html": "https://zenodo.org/doi/10.5281/zenodo.17882309", "self_iiif_manifest": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17882310/manifest", "self_iiif_sequence": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17882310/sequence/default", "files": "https://zenodo.org/api/records/17882310/files", "media_files": "https://zenodo.org/api/records/17882310/media-files", "thumbnails": {"10": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17882310:Recursive_Geometric_Entropy__A_Unified_Framework_for_Information_Theoretic_Shape_Analysis.pdf/full/%5E10,/0/default.jpg", "50": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17882310:Recursive_Geometric_Entropy__A_Unified_Framework_for_Information_Theoretic_Shape_Analysis.pdf/full/%5E50,/0/default.jpg", "100": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17882310:Recursive_Geometric_Entropy__A_Unified_Framework_for_Information_Theoretic_Shape_Analysis.pdf/full/%5E100,/0/default.jpg", "250": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17